WHEN crime statistics of the 2018/2019 year were released, Gauteng emerged to being the province with the most cases of driving under the influence of alcohol and drugs. With so many accidents, some of them really bad, the question SunWheels wants to ask you today, is what exactly must happen for you to do the right thing and stop drinking and driving? Asked for his take, the managing director of MasterDrive, Eugene Herbert, said regardless of efforts to educate and encourage drivers to avoid driving under the influence, there seems to be no positive impact. “People must take note of how to identify and what to do when they see a drunken driver on the road,” he said.